  "doc_id": "21879",
  "text": "In the present study, cell attachment was performed under static conditions. Fluidic conditions, such as microfluidic systems and cell rolling columns, are expected to amplify the variation in cell attachment [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] . Applying fluidic conditions is one way to improve cell enrichment efficiency. Compared with antibody-based cell enrichment, our method does not require any well-trained operators or special apparatuses. Additionally, cells enriched by our method are free from antibody-labeling, which is desirable for clinical applications.",
